28/09/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen says talks on settling Kosovo's final status could start in the middle of 2005, according to a report by the Beta news agency Monday (27 September).
This issue, as well as the involvement of Kosovo Serbs in regional dialogue, were described as the focus of his meetings with UN, NATO and OSCE officials in New York last week.
The Kosovo Contact Group meets in Vienna Tuesday, with representatives of Belgrade and Pristina participating.
Also Tuesday, EU security chief Javier Solana makes a brief visit to Pristina, where he is expected to reiterate calls for Kosovo Serbs to participate in the 23 October parliamentary elections.
Late Monday, a Serb home was damaged in a grenade attack in Mitrovica.
KFOR troops detonated a second grenade that had failed to explode.
(Reuters - 28/09/04;
Beta, B92, Tanjug - 27/09/04)
